      <body>
         <listPerson>
            <person sex="1">
               <persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n1">ጉግሳ፡ አርአያ፡</persName>
               <persName xml:lang="gez" type="normalized" corresp="#n1">Gugsā ʾArʾayā</persName>
               <occupation type="military">lǝʿul rās</occupation>
               <birth when="1882">1882</birth>
               <death when="1933-04-26">26th April 1933</death>
               <floruit notBefore="1910" notAfter="1933">He was a Tǝgrean nobleman who administrated <placeName ref="LOC6569Tegray">Tǝgrāy</placeName> together with his cousin <persName ref="PRS8802seyyumM">Śǝyyum Mangašā</persName>. 
                  In the struggle for the throne between <persName ref="PRS5620IyasuV">Lǝǧ ʾIyāsu</persName> and <persName ref="PRS5226haylase">Tafari Makʷannǝn</persName> he supported the latter. 
                  Later, during the coronation of <persName ref="PRS5226haylase">Tafari Makʷannǝn</persName> in <date when="1930">1930</date>, he was promoted from the title of rās (given to him by the Šawān elite) to lǝʿul rās. Occasionally he favoured the Italians who hoped for his support
                  the event of an open conflict with Ethiopia. Their hopes were never fulfilled, since Gugsā ʾArʾayā died of pneumonia in the meantime.
               </floruit>
            </person>
